block.translation:
Then Loki spake,the son of Laufey:

“As thy maid-servant thitherI go with thee;

We two shall hasteto the giants' home.”

Early it wasto evening come,

And forth was bornethe beer for the giants;

Thor alone ate an ox,and eight salmon,

All the dainties as wellthat were set for the women;

And drank Sif's matethree tuns of mead.
